Real life. 

Even animals can find it tough to survive in the ocean. Predators & human waste like plastic can kill these little creatures. 

Rare to find.  First in 10 years.  At least for me.  If he had been alive, I’d have put him back in the water.  Bittersweet. 

He’s going to our sea life museum in Rocky Point, MX where I live. Let the Pros study & help nature survive. 

Maybe the school children who come for tours can learn.  Perhaps one of them will grow up & become a marine biologist when he or she sees my little starfish & seashells we donate. 

Last week an adult sea turtle washed up on our beach. It was sad. I did not want to post those pictures here. Although sometimes I think it would be helpful if more people could understand not to throw debris over their boats or to stop using plastic, which can kill the small creatures. 🐚

#sealife #starfish #noplastic #saveouroceans #saveourplanet #4oceans

At what age do us women get comfy in our own skin? 

At 68, I believe aging barriers are lessening. I have so many people that encourage me to choose whatever future path I want in life with no hesitation to my age. Even the younger crowd. My 3 kids are my number one cheerleaders!

I don’t care about the scars on my body anymore. I’ve had my upper right lip replaced for skin cancer.  Hip replacements.  Both hips. That’s life…Let the scars show!

One of the best health decisions I made for myself was two years ago when I had breast implants removed. 

I figured with two titanium hips, I wanted everything else in my body real.  It was probably more mental than physical. I wanted to continue aging as healthy & natural as possible. 

I don’t object to any choices other women make for their own body. But for me, after my hip replacements…and then a stroke 4 years ago…the choice was made.

I wanted everything in my life as real as possible: Relationships. Food. My body. 

Focus on optimal health. 

Today:  I feel fantastic. Better than I have felt in a long time.  I love my body…faults & all.  I feel healthy at 68…post stroke.  Doubt breast implants had anything to do with a stroke but who knows? Maybe the body is working overtime to fight foreign objects?

Ladies, if you are considering breast implant removal, don’t be afraid of it. I love my new soft squishy boobs!  They’re not perfect but they’re me!  If you have any questions, DM me. 🤣🤪 
#breastimplantrevision #breastimplantremoval

As long as YOU love your life, you can be happy. Float outside YOUR comfort zone.  Give it a try.  Jump into the deep end. Try that ONE thing you’ve always wanted to do but never have. It may surprise you!

I miss her. 

Enjoy your time here. It’s short. One day our beautiful eyes won’t open to the morning sky. So love your life today. This moment. Right now!

How much is too much?

One day IG is your best friend.  The next…you’re walking on eggshells. 

I’m sharing tips THIS WEEK ONLY to help newer fashion influencers grow on IG or us ‘Old Timers’ refresh. Let me try to throw some positive vibes your way. 

Here’s 5 SUGGESTIONS to help grow a Fashion Page on IG today:

📌 SAVE this post and refer back when you need it. 

1️⃣ ENGAGE:  It’s essential!  But be honest:  How much time per day do you spend engaging?  Answer in comments. Be honest again: have you ever gotten the message from IG: “You cannot comment because we need to protect the community?”

YES!  You can engage too much.  IG MAY THINK YOU’RE SPAMMING & WILL CUT YOUR REACH/VIEWS. 

2️⃣ MAKE FRIENDS!!! The greatest asset in my ‘IG Treasure Box’ are friends. If you think you can ‘go it alone’…it’s going to take you twice as long to grow. (And life on IG is way more fun with friends) Share them in Stories & try to meet up if you can with others in your city/state. 

BUT…

Engaging leads me to important number 3:

3️⃣ ENGAGE CAREFULLY.  Take engaging in waves.  Don’t sit there all day engaging, copy/paste, or ‘hearting.’ Not only can it hurt your eyes, IG may think you’re spamming and ban you or cut you off. (“For the good of the Community.” YES!) 

Engage from your heart & take it slow.  Do it for an hour or so and then take a rest & come back to it. Switch to Stories. Don’t just heart. Send short words of goodwill or IG may force you to slow down. 

4️⃣ BE CAUTIOUS about tagging lots of friends in one post.  Again, IG may think you’re spamming. I’m extra super duper cautious on IG. 

5️⃣ BE CONSISTENT! I post at least several times a week. ENGAGE W EVERY POST first 30-60 minutes min & share to Stories ALWAYS!!!

OMG…IG is like the most jealous lover you’ve ever known! ☺️

Just MENTION someone else or for heaven’s sake…TALK TO THEM TOO MUCH or worst thing EVER….invite ANYONE to a party ‘OFF THE GRAM’…you may find yourself locked out of the house! 😂

Ok… maybe I am being a little extreme and exaggerating a wee bit…but NOT MUCH!!!

Am I getting my point across???

Welcome to the last in our series of ‘IG LOVES THIS!’

(Just cuz IG loves it doesn’t mean I do!) 🥰

Is anyone an IG Expert?  I think not. Way too fickle.  Yet I hope to share what SEEMS TO BE working for me.

IF YOU WANT more views, reach, likes, followers, FUN…IF THAT’S IMPORTANT to you: 

DO THESE 2 THINGS: 

1️⃣ Like, save, & share this post.  Come back to it the next time you’re posting.

2️⃣ STAY ON THE GRAM!!! 🤗
Create & edit your content on IG.  I film 90% of my reels in the App. My drafts are stored on IG. Download the good ones to your phone to save. 

Even if I use CapCut or other…I still will do some editing/speed/trimming in App. 

*STOP TAGGING/MENTIONING a zillion people (more than 3-5) in your posts. Or tons of unrelated hashtags.  Keep them few.  IG might think you’re ‘flirting too much’ & accidently consider you a spammer. You may receive notices stopping you from liking/commenting or removing your comments, etc. (For the good of the community😳) or worse yet…block you if you do it too much.

*SLOW IT DOWN!  Don’t engage too much. See my last post for more on this subject.

*STOP SAYING ‘LINK IN BIO.’ 
Don’t go off IG site for any reason & oh my goodness…

***STOP REFERRING FOLLOWERS OFF THE GRAM! 
Your reach & views may suffer. 

Instead try EX: ‘COMMENT DRESS.’ 

USE your COMMENTS field to mention/tag/refer!

I recently subscribed to an automated comment response co for links & it keeps followers on the Gram. Some say it increases engagement too?

Be creative.  Use keywords. Just TRY not to send people OFF THE GRAM. Some Collab clients are understanding this too lately.

We are all over 50.  Some of us are still raising babies. Others of us have already raised our babies and are now watching over grandbabies.

Do you believe age is just a number? Why do we even have a number behind our names? Perhaps it inspires our doctors…our children…our friends and family…to treat us with respect.

Or just the opposite…

The bigger the number…the less value society thinks we offer?

“What is the compensation?”

3️⃣ THE ART OF NEGOTIATION!!!

Learn how to respond to:

“We pay commission as compensation.”

In my mind, that’s not compensation. Or at least not the kind I’m referring to.

*Be relentless yet polite. It’s your biz.

My response: 

“Thank you for considering me.  I create brand awareness. Commission is only part of the compensation.”

They expect you to ask! 

I learned 75% of the clients I was doing gifted for had paid budgets. (Esp Amazon companies.) They didn’t offer it to me until I asked.

*Offer packages:
I rarely drop my starting fee but may add stories or more reels to the package price.

*Ask for HIGHER COMMISSION.

*Say “NO THANK YOU” if it isn’t feeling good.

Over time…You’ll be surprised how many companies will find $ in their budget for you. 😉
